                  </hi>. The prisoner is my son. On the 9th of July, at about eight o'clock, I put 19<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in a drawer in my chest, there were three half-crowns and three shillings and one sixpence—I went out about three o'clock in the afternoon and locked the prisoner in the house—on my return, in ten minutes, he was gone and the money also.</p>
